3 ways to elevate your photos
(I’m not an expert. I’m learning as I go. I have passion and am willing to share all my knowledge to help you discover yours.)
1. Have a clear intention. Ask yourself what will these pictures be used for? What audience do I want to see these photos? Does it match my branding and message? Does it reflect me?
2. Make sure your model can model. A pretty face doesn’t cut it, you need your model to understand micro movements and to always be in motion so your photos don’t look stagnant or too staged.
3. Have fun and be creative! Add little props or details. Play with angles or light to create different moods. As a lash artist we should focus on eyes so center your details around that so the eye is spotlighted. Think outside the box.
4. Check as you go. Snap some shots and look back at them… make sure you don’t have a rouge hair blocking your models eyes or a lash twisting sideways, that sort of thing 😉

We all want to be searched for easily and be able to attract traffic to our businesses so here are some: Tips for Naming your Business! 

💎Find a name that both the LLC and domain are available. Trust me, you want the .com. If it’s not available I suggest going back to the drawing board. Same goes for socials! 

💎Keep it simple. Less is more, no one wants to have to type out a long website name or something that is hard to spell. It will leave less room for error and you can avoid losing traffic to your site. 

💎Say it out loud. I know this sounds silly but make sure it’s easy to pronounce. Is it catchy? Does it roll off the tongue easily?

💎When in doubt, grab a thesaurus! 

If a client is asked about where she goes for her lashes, make it simple for her to share your info by following these tips! Make your business easily FOUND 🖤
